DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       The SSL_*_ctrl() family of functions is used to manipulate
       settings of the SSL_CTX and SSL objects. Depending on the
       command ccmmdd the arguments llaarrgg, ppaarrgg, or ffpp are evaluated.
       These functions should never be called directly. All
       functionalities needed are made available via other
       functions or macros.

